BACKGROUND: An increased body mass index (BMI) is associated with a high risk of 
cardiovascular disease and reduction in life expectancy. However, several 
studies reported improved clinical outcomes in obese patients treated for 
cardiovascular diseases. The aim of the present study is to investigate the 
impact of BMI on long-term clinical outcomes after implantation of zotarolimus 
eluting stents.
